The umpires get together to have a chat, and seem to have referred this to the TV umpire. Taken on the full, but I think the contact is well ahead of his body, and possibly wouldn't have been over waist height. Das gets the toe-end to this, and it is collected by the man inside the ring, as it doesn't travel a long way. It's a no-ball! Free hit to boot.

commentary: Mohammad Saifuddin to Madhevere, OUT caught at point! Saifuddin digs in another short one, rushing Madhevere, who tries to pull. The ball takes the shoulder of the bat, and balloons on the opposite side as that intended, being easily caught at point. Saifuddin is pumped, and raises his fist at the young Zimbabwean to send him off. The visitors had just started to find some traction with this stand, but it's been broken now, and Bangladesh are well on top

commentary: Mohammad Saifuddin to Sikandar Raza, OUT slower ball, and he has hit this down deep mid-wicket's throat! The fielder is actually three-quarters of the way into the boundary, and that's why it ends up being an easy catch for him in the end. Saif picks up another, and Raza's resistance comes to an end

commentary: Mohammad Saifuddin to Tshuma, OUT doesn't last more than one ball! Four for Saif, who bowls a searing in-swinging yorker to greet the number 11. It's difficult for anybody to deal with that first up, and more so for someone in just his second ODI. Saif does his typical cross-chested celebration, and the entire team now converges around Mashrafe Mortaza
